+      "sourceNotes": "Claim: Anthropic released the March 2026 Economic Index report, the third large-scale dataset on Claude usage | Source: VERIFIED (Anthropic, Economic Index report: Learning curves, March 2026, https://www.anthropic.com/research/economic-index-march-2026-report)\nClaim: Educational instruction tasks rose from 9% to 13% of all Claude conversations, the fastest-growing category | Source: VERIFIED (March 2026 Anthropic Economic Index: \"Educational instruction tasks have risen by more than 40 percent (from 9% to 13% of all conversations)\")\nClaim: Educational instruction tasks comprise 16% of Claude.ai conversations vs. 4% on the API | Source: VERIFIED (March 2026 Anthropic Economic Index: \"Claude.ai sees substantially more Educational Instruction tasks (16% vs. 4% on the API)\")\nClaim: 57% augmentation / 43% automation split in current Anthropic Economic Index | Source: VERIFIED (Anthropic Economic Index, March 2026 report, Claude.ai conversation sample, predominantly Claude Sonnet 4.5)\nClaim: Prior Index reported a 52% augmentation / 45% automation split | Source: VERIFIED (Earlier Anthropic Economic Index report: \"Augmentation (52% of conversations) has overtaken automation (45%)\")\nClaim: Week 4 of the pilot is the Discernment week | Source: GROUNDED (pilot_hub.html Week 4 section: \"You've used Claude for real tasks. Some outputs worked. Some needed significant rework. This is where you develop judgment.\")\nEditorial: Framing educational instruction as \"DC CAP's lane\" is Preston's synthesis tying the Index findings to the pilot's audience.\nEditorial: The phrase \"Education has moved into Claude's mainstream\" is Preston's framing.\nEditorial: The two-implication structure (sector-fit + augmentation rising) is Preston's pedagogical move, derived from the Index data.\nEditorial: \"Market check\" framing for what the Economic Index does for the pilot is Preston's.\nEditorial: The closing question \"what your team's split looks like, and whether it should\" is Preston's pedagogical close.\nAdversarial review 20260430: Em-dash count: 0. Banned phrases scanned and absent: leverage, utilize, delve, navigate, landscape, ecosystem, synergy, robust, holistic, stakeholders, foster, enhance, align, transformative, empower, spearhead, myriad, multifaceted, nuanced, pivotal, unpack, deep dive, however, moreover, furthermore, additionally, serves as, stands as, represents, functions as, at the end of the day, move the needle, to be clear, make no mistake, doing the heavy lifting, the real question, what most people miss, groundbreaking, game-changing, revolutionary, showcase, underscore. Contrastive \"not X, but Y\" constructions: 0. Rhetorical questions in body: 0. Declarative open: yes (cites Anthropic March 2026 Index release). Word count: 253.",
